\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch
\~ }
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\lang2057
Section 51, the final section in Part C of Chapter 5, permits the complainant to refer the complaint to the Tribunal where the Commission has issued a notice of non-referral either actual or deemed.\~  (Section 51(1)).}
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch
\~ }
\par \pard\plain \s17\sb0\sa120{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\fs24\lang2057
Any referral must be in the prescribed form and the Chairperson of the Tribunal must publish each referral in the Gazette and include in the notice certain specified details.\~  (Sections 51(2), (3) and (4)).}
